    "name": "Hyperbolic entailment cones",
    "description": "The text introduces a novel method for embedding directed acyclic graphs. This approach advocates for the use of hyperbolic spaces because they provably model tree-like structures better than Euclidean geometry. Furthermore, it models hierarchical relations as partial orders defined by nested geodesically convex cones. The method proves that these entailment cones admit an optimal shape with a closed form expression in both Euclidean and hyperbolic spaces, which canonically defines the embedding learning process. Experimentally, the method shows significant improvements over recent baselines regarding representational capacity and generalization.",
